ve planetary cores. We further find that the location of\nthe valley scales as $\\rho_{c*}^{-4/9}$ and that the observed planet population\nmust have predominantly rocky cores with typical water-ice fractions of less\nthan $\\sim 20\\%$. Furthermore, we show that the relative magnitude of the\nplanet occurrence rate above and below the valley is sensitive to the details\nof the planet-mass distribution but that the location of the valley is not.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Nov 2018 00:49:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 18 Apr 2019 04:30:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-27"}
